      "title": "👈 Samplers",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Sampler settings\n\nInference parameters aren't any different from normal Wan 2.2 generation. If you have a favorite sampler/scheduler combination for Wan generation, it will probably work fine here.\n\n> The default values assume the speedup lora is active.\n> - `steps: 4`\n> - `cfg: 1.0`\n\n> Without loras, use higher values.\n> - `steps: 20`\n> - `cfg: 3.5`\n\n\n"
      ],
      "color": "#233",
      "bgcolor": "#355"
    },
    {
      "id": 69,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        -5270,
        2210
      ],
      "size": [
        410,
        590
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 6,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "🚨Troubleshooting🚨",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# Troubleshooting\n\n- **The size of tensor a must match the size of tensor b at non-singleton dimension 1** - Check that both dimensions of your input videos are divisible by 16 and change this if they're not. Fun fact: 1080 is not divisible by 16!\n\n- **Regarding Framerate** - The Wan models are trained at 16 fps, so if your input videos are at some higher rate, you may get sub-optimal results. At the very least, you'll need to increase the number of context and replace frames by whatever factor your framerate is greater than 16 fps in order to achieve the same effect with VACE. I suggest forcing your inputs down to 16 fps for processing with this workflow, then re-interpolating back up to your desired framerate.\n\n- **Brightness/color shift** - VACE can sometimes affect the brightness or saturation of the clips it generates. I don't know how to avoid this tendency, I think it's baked into the model, unfortunately.\n  - My other VACE clip joiner workflow ([Github](https://github.com/stuttlepress/ComfyUI-Wan-VACE-Video-Joiner) | [CivitAI](https://civitai.com/models/2024299)) offers some options (crossfade, color matching) to reduce these artifacts.\n  - Disabling lightx2v speed loras can help, as can making sure you use the exact same lora(s) and strength in this workflow that you used when generating your clips. \n  - The most consistent mitigation I have found is to interpolate framerate up to 30 or 60 fps after using this workflow. The interpolation decreases how perceptible the color shift is. The shift is still there, but it's spread out over 60 frames instead over 16, so it doesn't look like a sudden change to our eyes any more. It's not perfect, but it gets you about 80% of the way there.\n\n- **Nodes 2.0** - The ComfyUI Nodes 2.0 renderer is an incomplete beta feature. It currently breaks a lot of workflows and custom nodes. I have not tested this workflow under Nodes 2.0, and I won't until Nodes 2.0 is a non-beta, fully implemented and unavoidable ComfyUI feature.\n\n- If you can't make the workflow work, update ComfyUI and try again. If you're not willing to update ComfyUI, I can't help you. We have to be working from the same baseline.\n\n- Feel free to [open an issue on github](https://github.com/stuttlepress/ComfyUI-Wan-VACE-Video-Joiner/issues). This is the most direct way to engage me. If you want a head start, paste your complete console log from a failed run into your issue."
      ],
      "color": "#322",
      "bgcolor": "#533"
    },
