      "title": "👈 Models",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Select your preferred Wan VACE, CLIP and VAE models\n> - Select a VACE model of the same model type and quantization that you run in your regular Wan generation workflow. If you usually run FP8 for video generation, choose FP8 VACE models. If you usually use Q4 GGUF, use Q4 GGUF VACE models.\n> - *The key to success and no OOM is to configure this workflow as close to your regular Wan workflow as possible.*\n> - **If you need GGUF models, replace these nodes with your favorite GGUF loaders.**\n"
      ],
      "color": "#233",
      "bgcolor": "#355"
    },
    {
      "id": 67,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        -2860,
        1910
      ],
      "size": [
        380,
        190
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 8,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "👆Speedup Loras",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Select Lightning/Lightx2v Loras\n> - Loras are enabled by default because that seems to be how most people do Wan generation.\n> - For best results, use the same lora models and lora strength that your input clips were generated with.\n> - Reducing lora strength or disabling the loras completely can reduce color/brightness artifacts.\n> - If you disable loras, don't forget to adjust sampler settings appropriately. See the **Samplers** note below."
      ],
      "color": "#233",
      "bgcolor": "#355"
    },
