      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "[Github](https://github.com/stuttlepress/ComfyUI-Wan-VACE-Video-Joiner) | [CivitAI](https://civitai.com/models/2277993) \n\n*Note: There is a heavier version of this workflow with more options available [here](https://civitai.com/models/2024299) or at the Github link above. It's useful for joining a large number of clips automatically. It also offers some methods for mitigating color/brightness shift that VACE can sometimes introduce.*\n\n---\n\n# How to Use This Workflow  \nMost of this information can also be found in the cyan notes scattered thoughout the workflow.\n\n## 1. Install the [*ComfyUI-Wan-VACE-Prep*](https://github.com/stuttlepress/ComfyUI-Wan-VACE-Prep) node pack.\n\nIt's a tiny package with no dependencies, so it is very unlikely to break your system, if you worry about such things.\n\nIf you don't already have the node, you can open the Manager and install it either from the *Missing Nodes* section, or search for **Wan VACE Prep**.\n\n## 2. Select models appropriate for your system\n- Select your VACE models in the *Load* group. \n- Select or disable speedup loras.\n\n## 3. Load your input videos  \nDrag and drop your input videos onto the **Load Video** nodes, or use the *choose file to upload* UI to select your videos. Both videos should be the same resolution and frame rate.\n\n## 4. Run the workflow\nThe joined video will be placed in your ComfyUI *output* directory, named something like `VACE joined_0001.mp4`\n"
      ],
      "color": "#146e47",
      "bgcolor": "#005a33"
    },
